# 4. 高みの覚悟

Shizuku: Good morning!
Shizuku: I'm Shizuku Hinomori from MORE MORE JUMP! Thank you for having me here today.
Staff Member: Yes, thank you for coming. We're almost ready to begin fitting you, so please have a seat and wait here.
Shizuku: Understood.
Shizuku: (All we're doing today is trying on our outfits for the shoot.)
Shizuku: (But everybody involved is here, so I have to stay focused.)
Yu: Hinomori.
Shizuku: Oh, Hagiyama...!
Yu: Once again, I look forward to working with you on this commercial.
Shizuku: Yes, I'm also looking forward to working with you.
Shizuku: You were so incredible during that audition. I promise to do everything I can in order to keep up with you.
Yu: Thank you... I really appreciate you saying that, Hinomori.
Shizuku: So, Hagiyama...
Shizuku: Can you tell me what was going through your mind during the audition?
Yu: What was going through my mind...?
Shizuku: Yes. I know it's a very open-ended question...
Shizuku: But I'd like to have a better understanding of your thought process, since we're going to be working together.
Shizuku: I want to know how you were able to shine so brilliantly that time.
Yu: ... I just...
Yu: My thought was... To pose in a way which exceeded everyone's expectations.
Shizuku: Their expectations...?
Yu: Yes.
Yu: I have to keep going above and beyond. My presence has to be powerful enough to blow others away.
Yu: I was sure that was the answer, so I decided to pose accordingly.
Yu: After all, the theme of this commercial demands that from us...
Yu: And more importantly, I think that's how a top idol ought to be, at all times.
Yu: But I'm still nowhere near that level. I have to keep finding ways to improve.
Shizuku: Hagiyama...
Shizuku: (But she's already so dazzling. Despite that, she still feels...)
Shizuku: (No, her resolve is precisely why her technical acuity is so high.)
Shizuku: (But I...)
Stylists: Okay! I'm seeing no issues with your outfit!
Stylists: Actually, I'm sorry... I need to quickly go ask about which accessories we'll be using, so would you mind waiting here for a bit? Call it a short break.
Shizuku: Yes, that's fine.
Shizuku: (It seems like they'll be done fitting me very soon...)
Shizuku: (Which means I need to begin strengthening my resolve in preparation for our shoot...)
Shizuku: (No... I can think that all I want, but I don't actually know how to do that...)
Shizuku: I'm sorry, but... I'd like to go for a bit of fresh air.
Shizuku: Phew...
Shizuku: (Keep it together... I can't let this chance slip.)
Oikawa's Voice: Yikes, what do we do now?
Shizuku: (Huh? Mr. Oikawa...? And that looks like the director, Mr. Saeki, next to him...)
Director: I don't know... Our client has every right to make this request, but as things stand, the balance just isn't there...
Oikawa: Right. Hinomori isn't bad for this...
Oikawa: But she sort of pales in comparison to Hagiyama's brilliant aura.
Shizuku: (Oh...)
Shizuku: (It's just as I suspected...)
Shizuku: (But I don't blame them for feeling that way. It's true, compared to her, I leave a lot to be desired in skill and in mindset...)
Shizuku: (I have to accept that, and keep finding ways to improve.)
Oikawa: Maybe asking Hinomori to audition was a mistake...
Director: Oh, were you the one who said to get her in to audition for this?
Oikawa: Yeah, it was me. We didn't stand to gain much since she doesn't belong to an agency, but I wanted to see that aura again.
Shizuku: (What...?)
Oikawa: You wouldn't believe how dazzling she was back then. She was just like Hagiyama. No, even more brilliant...
Shizuku: ...!
Shizuku: (Mr. Oikawa... He thought that highly of me...?)
Shizuku: (But to say I possessed an aura that was more brilliant than Hagiyama's seems...)
Oikawa: She told me herself. When I asked her why a fifteen-year-old girl like her had such a driven look about her.
Oikawa: She said...
Oikawa: “Because I'm the lead of Cheerful * Days.”
Director: Really...? Well, I guess anyone would feel that way if they were the lead of a group like Cheerful * Days.
Oikawa: *Nod* It just goes to show that people change when they have something to lose.
Director: True... That being said, if we don't see some improvement, then things aren't going to go well.
Oikawa: Right... If things don't immediately go well, then we'll have to redo the storyboards with Hagiyama as the sole focus.
Oikawa: It's a real shame, thinking about that brilliance. But at the end of the day, business is business.
Shizuku: ...!
Shizuku: (Mr. Oikawa asked me to audition because he was so impressed by the way I was back then...)
Shizuku: (But I'm falling short of his expectations...!)
Shizuku: (I don't want to disappoint him any further...!)
Shizuku: (Because if I fail here, then he and the others will likely never ask me to work with them ever again.)
Shizuku: (Not only will that affect my future, it may even jeopardize the future of MORE MORE JUMP!)
Shizuku: (I accepted this audition looking to lift everyone up. If I were to drag them down instead... No, I won't let that happen.)
Shizuku: I have to get myself together...!!
